# Plan Step Workflow

When the user asks to develop, start, or continue a plan step (e.g. "Start Part 3", "Develop Part 1"), run this checklist **before writing or editing any code**.

## 1. Identify the step

- Read `.docs/PLAN.md` and confirm the requested part number, scope, and **Goal**.
- Map the part to its branch name (see table below).

## 2. Branch check

Run `git branch --show-current`.

| Situation | Action |
|-----------|--------|
| On `main` | Create and checkout the part branch: `git checkout -b <branch-name>` |
| On the correct part branch | Stay on it |
| On a different part branch | Ask the user: finish current branch or switch? Do not switch silently |

### Branch names

| Part | Branch |
|------|--------|
| 1 | `part-01-contracts` |
| 2 | `part-02-ui-planning` |
| 3 | `part-03-scaffolding` |
| 4 | `part-04-frontend-base` |
| 5 | `part-05-auth` |
| 6 | `part-06-database` |
| 7 | `part-07-board-api` |
| 8 | `part-08-admin-panel` |
| 9 | `part-09-mcp` |
| 10 | `part-10-ai-chat` |
| 11 | `part-11-ai-sidebar` |

## 3. Resolve open issues first

- Read `.docs/branch-status.md` for the current branch.
- If any issue is unchecked (`- [ ]`), fix it before starting new work.
- After fixing, mark it solved (`- [x]`) in `.docs/branch-status.md`.
- Add new issues discovered during work as unchecked items under the current branch.

## 4. Report before implementing

Tell the user:

1. Current branch name
2. Open issues found and what was fixed (or "none")
3. Part goal from PLAN.md

Only after this report, begin implementation.
